<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870423-0057 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Nicor Inc.</HL><DD> 04/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GAS </IN><TEXT>   NICOR INC., Naperville, Ill., said shareholders at the annual meeting approved a fair price amendment that would require an 80% stock vote to approve some business combinations involving an interested holder, unless certain requirements are met, or approval is given by two-thirds of the continuing directors. The energy and natural gas distribution concern also said an amendment was approved to allow holders of voting stock to take action only at a duly called shareholders' meeting, with the exception of a board resolution allowing written consent for actions by preference and preferred stockholders. </TEXT></DOC>